com.camerontec.util.jmx.openmbean

Class BaseDynamicMBean

  • java.lang.Object
    • javax.management.NotificationBroadcasterSupport
      • com.camerontec.util.jmx.openmbean.BaseDynamicMBean
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    DynamicMBean, MBeanRegistration, NotificationBroadcaster, NotificationEmitter
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    BaseOpenMBean, ScriptsMBean

    public abstract class BaseDynamicMBean
extends NotificationBroadcasterSupport
implements DynamicMBean, MBeanRegistration
    This abstract class provides base services to be used by any dynamic MBean implementation.
    • Flexible caching of MBean info.
    • Automatic detection of typical error conditions:
      • Access to non-existing attributes or operations.
      • Attribute protection violations.
      • Attribute or operation return values non consistent with their exposed data type.
    • Normalized and consistent handling of exceptions thrown by underlying implementations.

        public AttributeList getAttributes(String[] attributeNames)
        Validates that the given attributes exist and are readable, then delegates the actual implementation to sub-classes, catching any throwable and mapping it to a JMX compliant exception as follows:

        • Error => RuntimeErrorException

      • valueIsCompatible

        protected boolean valueIsCompatible(MBeanAttributeInfo attributeInfo,
                                    Object value)
        Tells whether a value is compatible with the given attribute.

        This default implementation always returns true, but sub-implementations are free to provide a finer level of validation here.

        Returns:
        true iff. value is compatible with this attribute
